name: Roxane Ross
text: We saw the billboard from the highway and decided to go. It’s in the cute downtown area of Ozark, AL with plenty of parking. Coffee was delicious and the Boars Head breakfast sandwich was warm and fluffy! Great place and decor too with all the filled coffee burlap bags!!! It’s coffee time!

resp.text: Terrific. Thanks for stopping by and giving us a try. We really enjoy being downtown.

name: Tom Casassa
text: Nice folks, do their own roasting!  Love finding these kind of places in our little Alabama towns.  Very professional and friendly baristas make delicious coffee on a no BS espresso machine.  Alabama needs more of these.

resp.text: Thank you for the kind words. Yes we truly enjoy pulling shots on our espresso machine. It’s seriously legit.

resp.text: 🤙thanks

name: Zana Griffin
text:
I would love to speak to whomever is the owner of this new establishment to inform them of an incident I witnessed in their business regarding the way the staff poorly handled a situation involving a potentially homeless man.

Coffee taste great though.

In response to your reply:

Firstly, I'm truly sorry about what happened to your wife. I do hope she is doing ok from the interaction with the man.

And I am sorry to put it so plainly, and I don't mean to be unkind, but how are you even sure that you know who I am and what exactly is the issue I needed to address?

How are you sure that you were in the building at the same time I was - because a man who comes in 2 or 3 times a day happen to be there?

I don't believe our interactions are the same because you just informed me you wouldn't give him any coffee, but when I walked in he did have coffee, which led to the series of events that brought me here.

However, if you were there at the same time I was, as you assume, then you already know my complaint because you witnessed it happen, and perhaps do not believe it is warranted, and that really is all I need to know.

(When responding to the next Guest's concerns, please let them tell you what it is before assuming you know what the problem may be and volunteering a response -- once again, I truly am not trying to be rude - which is what delayed this response to find the kindest way to put it, because I have no desire in arguing with someone over the internet. I only reached out this way because it seemed the most professional and I work in the same industry and thought you as a owner of a new business would want to know. Just a kind suggest from someone who was very excited to have a local coffee shop, only to be let down on the first try.)

resp.text:
Update: Oh, so stop by anytime to let us know what you saw and are talking about because your comment popped up just minutes after he was violent so I assumed you were speaking about what I described below, sorry about that.

Glad you like our coffee.  What you missed about the incident was that the man started getting angry, yelling, and lunged at my wife in a violent manner.  My wife was simply talking to him.  I ran there to stop him from becoming more violent and I was about to call the police but he calmed down after I spoke strongly to him.  After he calmed down he asked us for free coffee, we always give him free coffee when he stops by (sometimes he stops by two or three times a day).  I said no coffee because he was angry and mean and told him to leave.  I'm sorry you didn't like the way I handled the situation but I was concerned he was going to get violent but I’m sure glad he didn’t.

Consistently the worst experience.  Want a sandwich with tomatoes?  They're out of tomatoes.  Want a sandwich with cucumbers? Out of cucumbers.  What about a bagel sandwich with bacon?  Out of bagels and bacon.  How about customer service?  All out of that too. But there's plenty of awful selection and rude attitude directed at their customers.

I went back to ask about my missing bacon and was rudely told "We don't have no bacon", then the employee stormed off.  I will forego lunch and drive off campus from now on; no more 3-4x weekly visits to this awful place.

name: cottonwood rescue
text:
Dunkin' let me tell y’all about the team at 1865 E. Main St. Dothan😍 This team is always the most friendly and helpful I have ever experienced at Dunkin’💯 & I have visited them from Panama City Beach to Tallahassee, to Birmingham to Gainesville & no other compares to my home store!🤞🏼As an Emt I’m on the go with 911 ALL day & believe me we are blazing the roads all day to and from the hospital. & I know if I need a pick me up I will only stop at this location. They know how to get my coffee fix prompt and exactly how I like it. 90% of the time they see me pull up on the ambulance and they already have my order going before I make it in the store! I know they have to be tired of seeing me but they always greet me with a smile on their faces! I couldn’t ask for better service and great personalities!  It’s the “Be safe out there today.” For me! 🥲 Y’all are just as essential as I am and I thank y’all for your service!  & keep being great!☺️

With much love always!💕☕️

- a very great full EMT🚑💙

name: Matthew Pearson
text:
If you're a UAB student, just go here.. Skip Panera and Starbucks if you're looking for food. The sandwiches here are SO MUCH better than Panera. I mean in another league. And they cost less.

I have yet to try their coffee, but as they seem to serve caribou coffee, I am sure it will be more than adequate. I will be skipping Starbucks except when I am in the mood for a frappuccino.

YES it is worth the walk(not really far from anything anyways). Even better if you live in Blazer or NFR.

It may not be the absolute best food out there, but for UAB students with dining dollars? Best I've had. That is unless you want a burger.

tl;dr Best food I've had at UAB unless you're craving for a burger, then go the Den.

name: notthebeesxoxo
text:
This is the best DD in town. I love DD coffee but struggled for a while to find a DD that can consistently make a drink right. Every place, they either made it too strong, not strong enough, not sweet enough, too sweet... Just tons of issues and lots of wasted money on coffees I couldn't even force myself to finish.

Then they opened this location and they are the most consistent DD I've been to and I go here every single day during the week. The people are also so nice and the drive thru, even when busy, is so fast! There could be 7 cars in line and I'll still be done in 10 mins or less.

text: Horrible experience. Absolutely awful. I ordered two drinks it was SUPPOSED to be a Iced Mocha Coffee and a Chai Latte, instead I got two coffee flavored waters. The coffee was so watered down that the Iced Mocha only had a after taste of coffee. The Chai lattee was so watered down that I couldn't even taste the Chai. Our drinks were literally water. Don't even get me started on the wait time. We were the only people ordering and waiting for our food and it still took them 15 minutes to make our drinks. I won't be coming back. I went toward the middle of August.

resp.text: Thank you for your review.  I also enjoyed your review of the Sims 4 Vampire Expansion on your Youtube channel.  Looking at our transaction history, we haven't sold a Chai Latte recently. If you would kindly let me know when you visited Daily Bagel in Pell City, AL, I will be happy to issue you a refund for your drinks. Thanks!
